The Internal Revenue Service defines your dependent as someone who meets
all of the following conditions with relation to you:
    * Is your son, daughter, stepchild, or foster child
    * Is under age 19 and younger than you, or is a student under 24 and
    and younger than you, or is permanently disabled
    * Did not provide over half of his or her support
    * Did not file a joint tax return or field or joint return only to claim
    a refund
    * Lived with you for more than half a year

Using a single chain of predicates, determine is your child dependent or not